      "comments": [
        {
          "author": "richsalz",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "body": "Making a PQ/T hybrid recommended is one thing.  Make traditional KX be not recommended should be argued in a separate draft.",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-28T22:42:40Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-04-28T22:42:40Z"
        }
      ],
      "reviews": [
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDORWyibc70vefx",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "92c093a"
          },
          "author": "muhammad-usama-sardar",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "state": "CHANGES_REQUESTED",
          "body": "Personally, I am strongly opposed to this PR. My strong preference is that we should not let (arguably unnecessary) debates on traditionals stand in the way of recommending the hybrids. The former can be done separately later on in a new draft.",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-14T13:02:42Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-04-14T13:02:42Z",
          "comments": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "number": 3,
      "id": "PR_kwDORWyibc7SQyPD",
      "title": "Recommend SecP256r1MLKEM768 and SecP384r1MLKEM1024 as well",
      "url": "https://github.com/bwesterb/draft-westerbaan-tls-keyshare-recommendations/pull/3",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "bwesterb",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "",
      "createdAt": "2026-04-14T09:46:01Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-04-28T21:26:42Z",
      "baseRepository": "bwesterb/draft-westerbaan-tls-keyshare-recommendations",
      "baseRefName": "main",
      "baseRefOid": "5776ff5c934e1a31d2b0536c2bab4516836da783",
      "headRepository": "bwesterb/draft-westerbaan-tls-keyshare-recommendations",
      "headRefName": "recommend-all-three",
      "headRefOid": "e0664d0eeee7015c81991df0060e8fdcbbb49421",
      "closedAt": null,
      "mergedAt": null,
      "mergedBy": null,
      "mergeCommit": null,
      "comments": [
        {
          "author": "bwesterb",
          "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
          "body": "There have been some people in favor of this change, hence I created the PR for discussion. Personally I dislike it: there is a real risk in fragmenting the ecosystem. Also there is little difference between the P256 and X25519 hybrid. The P256 is available anyway, why the need to recommend it?",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-14T12:37:17Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-04-14T12:37:17Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "muhammad-usama-sardar",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "body": "> there is a real risk in fragmenting the ecosystem\r\n\r\nI don't think recommending 2 more leads to \"real risk\" of fragmentation.",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-28T16:13:17Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-04-28T16:13:17Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "davidben",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "body": "@bwesterb is right. The way key shares work in TLS, until draft-ietf-tls-key-share-prediction is deployed, there is a real cost to having two of these.",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-28T21:12:19Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-04-28T21:12:19Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "bwesterb",
          "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
          "body": "`draft-ietf-tls-key-share-prediction` solves the performance cost. It doesn't solve the security issue where different peers might choose different key shares due to limited resources, be they for hardware or development.",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-28T21:19:18Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-04-28T21:19:50Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "davidben",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "body": "Oh definitely. I just meant that draft is needed before extra key shares are not *disproportionately* more expensive. Even after that's resolved, we still pick up the general costs around fragmentation. I.e. I agree with you that this draft shouldn't extend to the other ones. :-)",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-28T21:26:42Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-04-28T21:26:42Z"
        }
      ],
